observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our recommendation that the LCE:

(a) create an Inventory Committee (IC) that will execute the physical inventory of the PPEs owned by the Municipality and submit the RPCPPE to the audit team; 

(b) require the Municipal Accountant and the Property Custodian to (i) reconcile their records with the results of physical inventory of PPE upon completion and preparation of the report by the IC; and (ii) maintain updated property records.

We recommended that the LCE and the Municipal Environment and Natural Resources Office (MENRO):

(a) involve closely the barangay officials in solid waste management and activate the Solid Waste Management Committees in every barangay for the strict enforcement and continuous implementation of the existing environmental laws especially on establishment of MRF and waste segregation at source; 

(b) intensify information campaign on solid waste management and educate the constituents on the necessity of   the construction of MRF in every barangay and establishing programs on composting, recycling, re-use, and recovery of solid waste generated; 
(c) consider extending financial assistance, resources, and technology to all of the ten barangays which remained non-compliant to the basic requirements of R.A. No. 9003; and 

(d) develop waste reduction programs such as composting, recycling, re-use, and recovery of solid waste generated in order to reduce hauling and disposal costs of the Municipality.

(a) formulate detailed policy guidelines concurred by the SB, in the granting  of various types of financial assistance parallel to the provisions of the DSWD MC to ensure that only those qualified constituents in crisis situation are extended financial assistance;

(b) ensure that all payments must be made by check issued directly under the name of the beneficiary or in the form of cash advance of the disbursing officer in the Treasury Office; and 

(c) instruct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that all payments are adequately and properly supported by required documents prior to payment.

